                <note><hi rend="italic">The Journal of Negro History</hi> was founded in 1916 by Dr. Carter G. Woodson, as one of the first journals to cover African American history. Though Chesnutt was consistently a subscriber to the journal, he did not contribute any publications.</note>
            </object>
